   182	### D.4 setup-experiment.sh sequencing — option (a) selected
   183	
   184	`setup-experiment.sh` already runs the bare-repo seed step
   185	synchronously via `compose run --rm --no-deps eden-repo-init`.
   186	This sub-chunk extends that pattern: setup-experiment now also
   187	**brings Gitea up** synchronously (before the rest of the stack)
   188	and provisions it before writing the operator's next-step
   189	instructions. No deferred work in the operator's own
   190	`compose up`.
   191	
   192	Concrete sequence (replaces the current "seed bare repo, write
   193	.env, exit" flow):
   194	
   195	1. Generate / preserve all secrets (existing flow), including
   196	   the new `GITEA_REMOTE_PASSWORD`.
   197	2. Write the partial `.env` (without `EDEN_BASE_COMMIT_SHA` —
   198	   filled in step 7).
   199	3. **Bring Gitea up:**
   200	   `docker compose --env-file "$ENV_FILE" up -d --wait gitea`
   201	   (uses Gitea's existing healthcheck).
   202	4. **Provision Gitea** per §D.3 (eden user, access token, repo).
   203	5. **Write the credential-helper script** under
   204	   `${COMPOSE_DIR}/.gitea-creds-${EXPERIMENT_ID}/`.
   205	6. **Seed + push** via `compose run --rm --no-deps eden-repo-init`,
   206	   which now takes a `--push-to <url>` flag and pushes the seed
   207	   commit to Gitea after creating the local bare repo.
   208	7. Capture the seed SHA, replace the `.env` placeholder
   209	   (existing pattern).
   210	8. Print operator next-steps (existing — `compose up -d --wait`).
   211	
   212	The shared `eden-bare-repo` volume is removed from `compose.yaml`
   213	in the cutover; `eden-repo-init` keeps writing to it locally only
   214	so the seed-and-push step is self-contained, then the volume is
   215	discarded by the existing `compose down -v` posture.
   216	
   217	**Idempotency:** all four provisioning operations (user create,
   218	token mint, repo create, ref push) are idempotent. Re-running
   219	setup-experiment with the same env file is a no-op for Gitea
   220	state. Re-running with a NEW env file (different
   221	`GITEA_REMOTE_PASSWORD`) updates the user's password via
   222	`gitea admin user change-password`.
