   224	### D.5 Per-service compose changes
   225	
   226	Each worker host gains:
   227	
   228	- A *private* named volume for its clone:
   229	  `eden-implementer-repo`, `eden-evaluator-repo`,
   230	  `eden-orchestrator-repo` (no shared `eden-bare-repo` anymore).
   231	- The credential-helper script bind-mounted RO at
   232	  `/etc/eden/credential-helper.sh`.
   233	- A new `--gitea-url <http-url>` CLI flag on each host.
   234	
   235	Each worker host's startup logic:
   236	
   237	1. If `/var/lib/eden/repo` is not yet a git repo, `clone_from`
   238	   from Gitea via `clone --bare` (per §D.8a — all worker hosts
   239	   are bare clones).
   240	2. Otherwise, `git fetch --prune origin '+refs/heads/*:refs/heads/*'`
   241	   to refresh local heads and prune any local heads that no
   242	   longer exist on the remote (one-shot orphan cleanup as a
   243	   fetch side effect).
   244	3. **Integrator-only: reconcile orphan REMOTE refs.** The
   245	   orchestrator's startup additionally walks the remote
   246	   `refs/heads/trial/*` via `git ls-remote origin
   247	   'refs/heads/trial/*'`. For each ref the spec gives us a
   248	   **machine-parseable artifact** at the commit tip — chapter 6
   249	   §3.2 mandates the squash commit's tree contains
   250	   `.eden/trials/<trial_id>/eval.json`. The reconciliation
   251	   reads `<commit_sha>:.eden/trials/` via `git ls-tree --name-only
   252	   <commit_sha> .eden/trials/` to recover the trial_id (a
   253	   single subdir name; reject if zero or more than one — that
   254	   commit isn't a valid integrator squash). Then the
   255	   integrator calls `Store.read_trial(trial_id)`:
   256	   - If the trial doesn't exist OR has no `trial_commit_sha`
   257	     (i.e., `trial.integrated` was never committed), issue
   258	     `delete_remote_ref` against Gitea to clean up.
   259	   - Otherwise the trial is properly integrated; leave the ref
   260	     alone.
   261	
   262	   This is the recovery rule for the §D.6 step-4a failure mode
   263	   ("remote publish succeeded, store write failed, remote
   264	   compensating delete failed") AND for transport-indeterminate
   265	   step-2 failures whose post-failure read-back also failed (the
   266	   only case §D.7d's branch-decision-tree leaves to the sweep).
   267	   The trial_id-from-tree path is spec-authoritative; ref-name
   268	   parsing is not, since the spec treats trial_id as opaque.
   269	   Branch names happen to follow `trial/<trial_id>-<slug>` as a
   270	   reference-impl convention, but the integrator's reconciliation
   271	   does NOT depend on that convention.
   272	4. Enter the normal poll loop.
   273	
   274	**Per-operation freshness for long-lived clones.** The orchestrator
   275	loop and the web-ui's admin/implementer modules are long-lived;
   276	remote refs change under their feet between the startup fetch and
   277	the next operation. Two policies:
   278	
   279	- **Read-before-write:** any service path that's about to write a
   280	  ref via `repo.create_ref` first runs `git fetch origin <ref>`
   281	  to refresh its local view. This keeps `--force-with-lease`'s
   282	  expected-old-sha aligned with the remote.
   283	- **Read-before-display:** the web-ui admin work-refs GC page
   284	  (chunk-9e) runs `git fetch origin '+refs/heads/work/*:refs/heads/work/*'`
   285	  on every GET so the operator's view matches the remote. The
   286	  per-op fetch budget here is one HTTP roundtrip + a small ref
   287	  list, well under 100ms in the reference deployment.
   288	
   289	Failure mode: if Gitea is unreachable at startup, the host exits
   290	non-zero and compose's `restart: on-failure` (existing posture)
   291	retries until healthy. Mid-operation Gitea unreachability raises
   292	`GitTransportError` from `eden_git`; service-level handlers catch
   293	it role-specifically per [chapter 3](../../spec/v0/03-roles.md):
   294	
   295	- **Implementer** (chapter 3 §3.3): infrastructure faults during
   296	  worker-side execution map to `ImplementSubmission(status="error",
   297	  trial_id=..., commit_sha=None)`. The trial composite-commits
   298	  to `error` atomically with the task transition. Same posture
   299	  as today's chunk-10d "subprocess timeout" path.
   300	- **Evaluator** (chapter 3 §4.4): infrastructure faults map to
   301	  `EvaluateSubmission(status="eval_error", trial_id=..., metrics=None)`.
   302	  The trial stays at its prior status (`success` from the
   303	  implementer) so the trial can be re-evaluated; this is the
   304	  spec-mandated distinction between `error` (worker-determined
   305	  bad outcome) and `eval_error` (infrastructure failure).
   306	- **Integrator** (chapter 6 §3.4): two distinct cases.
   307	  - A **definite remote rejection** (`RefRefused`) on `push_ref`
   308	    means the remote did not accept the ref — only step 1's
   309	    local create exists, and step 4b's local rollback alone is
   310	    sufficient.
   311	  - A **transport-indeterminate failure** (`GitTransportError`)
   312	    on `push_ref` means we don't know if the remote accepted —
   313	    the ack was lost. We MUST disambiguate by immediately
   314	    running `git ls-remote origin <ref>`:
   315	    - If the remote ref is absent → rollback step 4b (local) only.
   316	    - If the remote ref equals our pushed SHA → the push DID
   317	      land, so run BOTH 4a (remote delete) and 4b (local).
   318	    - If the remote ref exists at a different SHA → another
   319	      integrator integrated a different commit on the same
   320	      trial id; this is `RefRefused` semantics, run 4b only.
   321	    - If `ls-remote` itself transport-fails (Gitea still down)
   322	      → log critical-severity and rely on §D.7c's startup sweep
   323	      to clean up. This is the only case where an orphan can
   324	      persist across the integrator restart, and the sweep is
   325	      its backstop.
   326	  - A transport failure during `delete_remote_ref` (step 4a)
   327	    falls through to §D.7c likewise.
