   514	## Tests
   515	
   516	Three tiers, each driving the **public entry point** the
   517	production code calls (per the AGENTS.md "test the actual code
   518	path" pitfall) — no helper-only assertions.
   519	
   520	### Unit (`reference/packages/eden-git/tests/test_remote_ops.py`)
   521	
   522	Run against a local file-URL git remote (`file:///path/to/bare`)
   523	— no Gitea daemon, no http. Sufficient because git's transport
   524	abstraction makes file:// share the same ref-update code path as
   525	http:// for our four new operations.
   526	
   527	- `GitRepo.clone_from(url=file://…, dest=…)` produces a working
   528	  clone at `dest`.
   529	- `GitRepo.push_ref(ref, expected_old_sha)` succeeds when the
   530	  remote ref matches `expected_old_sha`; raises `RefRefused`
   531	  when the remote has diverged.
   532	- `GitRepo.fetch_ref(ref)` updates the local ref to match
   533	  remote; returns the fetched SHA.
   534	- `GitRepo.delete_remote_ref(ref, expected_sha)` succeeds when
   535	  the remote matches; raises `RefRefused` on divergence; raises
   536	  `RefRefused` (not silent success) when the remote ref is
   537	  already gone (idempotency caveat: callers handle the
   538	  already-gone case explicitly because chapter-6 §3.4
   539	  rollback semantics distinguish "no-op" from "won the race").
   540	- Credential-helper roundtrip: drive a real `git http-backend`
   541	  via Python's `http.server` + the helper script generated by
   542	  setup-experiment's template. Assert that without the helper
   543	  the push fails 401, with the helper the push succeeds. This
   544	  proves the helper is wired correctly end-to-end at unit
   545	  speed; argv-only inspection would NOT.
   546	
   547	### Integration (`reference/packages/eden-git/tests/test_remote_integrator.py`)
   548	
   549	Drive the **public `Integrator.integrate(trial_id)` method**
   550	through each failure mode, using a real local-file remote +
   551	a monkey-patched Store:
   552	
   553	- Happy path: `integrate` succeeds → local ref + remote ref +
   554	  `trial.integrated` event all present.
   555	- Push race (step 2 fails): set the remote `trial/<trial_id>-<slug>` ref to
   556	  a different SHA before `integrate` runs. Assert: local ref
   557	  rolled back, remote untouched, no `trial.integrated` event.
   558	- Store failure after push (step 3 fails): monkeypatch
   559	  `Store.integrate_trial` to raise `DispatchError`. Assert:
   560	  remote ref deleted (compensating push), local ref deleted,
   561	  no `trial.integrated` event.
   562	- Compensating delete itself fails (step 4a fails): monkeypatch
   563	  `delete_remote_ref` to raise `GitTransportError`. Assert:
   564	  the integrator logs a critical-severity diagnostic AND the
   565	  next-startup reconciliation pass (§D.7c) cleans up the orphan
   566	  on Gitea. (Tested via a second `Integrator()` instance after
   567	  the first's failure.)
   568	
   569	### Smoke (`compose-smoke-*` extensions)
   570	
   571	Extends both `compose-smoke` and `compose-smoke-subprocess(-docker)`
   572	with one new post-quiescence assertion:
   573	
   574	```bash
   575	git ls-remote http://eden:${GITEA_REMOTE_PASSWORD}@gitea:3000/eden/${EXPERIMENT_ID}.git \
   576	    | grep -E 'refs/heads/trial/' | wc -l
   577	```
   578	
   579	≥3 (matches the existing `trial.integrated` event count
   580	assertion). Proves the remote actually has the integrated trial
   581	refs, not just the local clones.
   582	
   583	A new `compose-e2e` extension covers the chunk-9e admin
   584	work-refs GC page driving a `delete_remote_ref` against Gitea
   585	(asserts the remote ref is gone after the operator-clicks-delete
   586	flow).
   587	
   588	### `eden_git` testing scope: file-URL is enough
   589	
   590	The new unit + integration tests use `file://` URLs for the
   591	remote. We do NOT add a `pytest.mark.gitea` marker. Justification:
   592	
   593	- `git push --force-with-lease` and `git push --delete` use the
   594	  same wire protocol over file:// as over http://. The CAS
   595	  semantics are server-side (the remote's reflog), not transport-
   596	  dependent.
   597	- HTTP transport is exercised end-to-end by the smoke scripts
   598	  against the real Gitea container — that's where any
   599	  http-specific issue (auth, redirect, content-length, etc.)
   600	  surfaces.
   601	- A separate marker would split coverage and require yet another
   602	  CI service container (Gitea), with no proof that http exposes
   603	  bugs the file:// path doesn't already catch.
   604	
   605	The credential-helper unit test is the one exception: it spins
   606	up a tiny http server in-process so the auth round-trip is real,
   607	no external dependency needed.
   608	
   609	## F-T. Cutover blast-radius inventory
   610	
   611	Concrete file count from `grep -l "init_bare\|GitRepo.*bare"`
   612	across the repo (excluding READMEs):
   613	
   614	- **`reference/packages/eden-git/tests/`** (4 files —
   615	  `test_repo_branches_worktrees.py`, `test_repo_plumbing.py`,
   616	  `test_environment_isolation.py`, `conftest.py`) — these
   617	  exercise local-only `GitRepo` ops; they STAY on local-only
   618	  paths because the new ops are tested separately in
   619	  `test_remote_ops.py`.
   620	- **`reference/packages/eden-git/src/eden_git/repo.py`** — the
   621	  module under modification. New methods land here.
   622	- **Service tests that init a local bare repo:**
   623	  - `reference/services/_common/tests/test_worktrees.py` — pure
   624	    worktree behavior, no remote — STAYS local.
   625	  - `reference/services/planner/tests/test_planner_subprocess.py`
   626	    — planner doesn't touch git refs (only proposals) — STAYS
   627	    local.
   628	  - `reference/services/implementer/tests/test_implementer_subprocess.py`,
   629	    `test_host.py` — these exercise `_run_subprocess` and
   630	    submit flows. The implementer change in §D.7 adds a single
   631	    `repo.push_ref` call after the existing `repo.create_ref`.
   632	    Tests gain a tiny bare-repo `init --bare` as the local
   633	    "remote" + assertion that `push_ref` was invoked. Net
   634	    change per test: ~5 lines.
   635	  - `reference/services/evaluator/tests/test_evaluator_subprocess.py`
   636	    — evaluator gains `fetch_ref` before worktree-add. Same
   637	    pattern: local "remote" + one-line assertion.
   638	  - `reference/services/orchestrator/tests/test_e2e.py`,
   639	    `test_subprocess_e2e.py` — these are the heavyweights.
   640	    Each spawns the full 5-process stack against an in-memory /
   641	    sqlite store. Adding a real local file-URL remote here
   642	    means: setUp creates `tmp_path/remote.git` as a bare repo,
   643	    the test's `seed_bare_repo` pushes to it, each spawned
   644	    service gets `--gitea-url file://<path>` instead of
   645	    `--repo-path <path>`. Net change per file: ~30 lines, no
   646	    new processes. Both tests are already `pytest.mark.e2e`,
   647	    skipped on Windows.
   648	
   649	**Total file changes for the cutover:** ~14 source files modified,
   650	plus ~3 new files. Tests that don't touch a real bare repo
   651	(everything in `_common/tests/test_common.py`, web-ui non-flow
   652	tests, contracts tests, storage tests) are entirely unaffected.
   653	
   654	The "most existing tests can stay on local-only paths" claim is
   655	defensible because the **only** tests that previously exercised
   656	the implementer/evaluator/integrator flows did so against an
   657	in-process bare repo on disk; switching that bare repo to be
   658	the remote (via `file://`) and adding a tiny local working clone
   659	is mechanical — no new architecture surfaces.
   660	
   661	## Verification
   662	
   663	1. `uv run pytest -q` — full suite + new unit tests + new
   664	   `test_remote_integrator.py` integration tests pass. (No
   665	   `pytest.mark.gitea` marker — see §F-Tests for why
   666	   `file://` is sufficient at unit/integration speed; HTTP
   667	   transport is exercised by the smokes against the real
   668	   Gitea container.)
   669	2. `bash healthcheck/smoke.sh` — host-mode smoke passes,
   670	   workers actually push to Gitea, integrator promotes via
   671	   Gitea (asserted via `git ls-remote`).
   672	3. `bash healthcheck/smoke-subprocess.sh` and
   673	   `bash healthcheck/smoke-subprocess-docker.sh` — same.
   674	4. `bash healthcheck/e2e.sh` — Web UI flow still passes; Web UI
   675	   implementer module now pushes to Gitea on submit.
   676	5. CI: all 11 jobs green; no new required jobs in this chunk
   677	   (per the chunk-10d / 10e posture).
   678	
   679	## Out of scope
   680	
   681	- **Gitea HA / multi-instance.** Single Gitea, single bare-repo
   682	  there. HA is a Phase 12+ control-plane concern.
   683	- **SSH or HTTPS-with-TLS instead of plain HTTP.** SSH key
   684	  management and TLS termination are their own follow-ups; plain
   685	  HTTP Basic is enough for the reference (Gitea is on the
   686	  compose internal network only; the same soft-boundary as the
   687	  existing reference posture).
   688	- **Gitea webhooks.** The orchestrator polls `Store` directly
   689	  for state; Gitea doesn't need to notify anyone.
   690	- **Multi-experiment Gitea.** This chunk creates ONE repo per
   691	  experiment, named after the experiment id. Coexistence of
   692	  multiple experiments on the same Gitea works naturally
   693	  (different repo names) but no special wiring.
   694	- **Branch protection inside Gitea.** The reference relies on
   695	  CAS at the git layer (`--force-with-lease`); a Gitea-side
   696	  branch protection rule would be redundant.
   697	- **Updating branch protection on the GitHub side** to require
   698	  any new CI job. Same posture as 10c/10d/10e/follow-up-A.
   699	
   700	## Risks
   701	
   702	- **Local ref + remote push atomicity.** Between the local
   703	  `create_ref` and the remote `push_ref` there's a window
   704	  where the local ref exists but the remote doesn't. If the
   705	  worker host crashes there, the next startup's `git fetch
   706	  --prune` removes the local-only orphan as a side effect
   707	  (covers `work/*`). For local-only orphan `trial/*` refs in
   708	  the orchestrator's clone, the same prune-on-fetch removes
   709	  them. For orphan `trial/*` refs that ended up REMOTELY
   710	  published (the §D.6 step-4a-failed case), §D.7c's
   711	  store-authoritative reconciliation pass handles cleanup at
   712	  integrator startup.
   713	- **Credential exposure.** The credential-helper script lives
   714	  on the host filesystem with mode 0755 (executable; mounted
   715	  ro into the worker). Any process on the host with read
   716	  access can grab the password. This matches the existing
   717	  soft-isolation posture; documented in §7 of the
   718	  reference-binding chapter alongside the existing DooD
   719	  caveats. Hardened deployments substitute Docker secrets,
   720	  Vault, or sysbox-isolated workers; the wrap shape is

